==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

{{Han compound|竹|合|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=bamboo}}. Originally, it was a variant of [[荅]], where the semantic component [[艸]] (grass) was later mistakenly replaced by [[竹]] (bamboo). It expresses the meaning of "to respond."<ref>Digital Shinjigen 2017</ref>

====References====
{{reflist}}

===Etymology===
Cognate with {{och-l|對|to respond}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}), which is the [[exoactive]] of {{och-l|答}}. Compare {{cog|bo|འདེབས||to cast; to send}} ({{zh-ref|Hill, 2019}}).

